The scroll-to-bottom button still works — I didn't remove the `scrollToBottom` function itself. I only removed the **duplicate return key**. Before my change, it returned:

```ts
return {
  scrollToBottom,                          // ← never destructured by any consumer
  handleScrollToBottomClick: scrollToBottom, // ← the one Chat.tsx actually uses
  syncGeometry,
};
```

`Chat.tsx` only destructures `handleScrollToBottomClick` (line 148), never `scrollToBottom` directly. The button still calls `handleScrollToBottomClick` which is still `scrollToBottom` under the hood. No behavior change.

